===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|larvae|larvæ}}

# An early stage of growth for some [[insect]]s and [[amphibian]]s, in which after hatching from their egg, insects are wingless and resemble a [[caterpillar]] or [[grub]], and amphibians lack limbs and resemble [[fish]].
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1923| title=Bulletin of the U.S. Department of Agriculture|author=| page=6| passage=The habits of the second nymphal stage are likewise similar to those of the '''larva''' stage. }}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1954| title=Contribution - Hawaii Marine Laboratory |author=| page=186| passage=Several possible explanations are advanced for a large decrease in numbers between the egg and '''larva''' stage, namely, drift of larvae from the sampling station, escape through the meshes of the net, sinking below the surface layers, and loss from mortality. A seasonally erratic egg to '''larva''' ratio is pointed out.}}
# An animal in the aforementioned stage.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1920| title=Memoirs of the Department of Agriculture in India|author=| page=84| passage=The young '''larva''' bores into the tissue of a tobacco leaf, usually near the place where it has emerged from the egg, in cases where the egg was laid on a leaf, and mines into the leaf. }}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2020| title=Ichthy, diary of a newt larva |author=Anne Sagner | page=4| passage=What does a mountain newt '''larva''' eat? }}
# A form of a recently born or hatched animal that is quite different from its adult stage.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1968| title=Elements of Marine Ecology |author=R. V. Tait & F. A. Dipper| page=344| passage=In water of 5-6° C, herring hatch in about 22 days, at 11-12° C in 8–10 days. The newly hatched '''larva''' is about 6–8 mm long and at first depends on the food reserves of the yolk-sac. }}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2014| title=Atlas of Crustacean Larvae |author=Joel W. Martin, ‎Jørgen Olesen, ‎Jens T. Høeg | page=199| passage=Breeding females of both the Lophogastrida and Mysida carry their embryos and '''larvae''' in a marsupium, within which their entire embryonic and larval development takes place.}}
# {{lb|en|figurative}} A [[preliminary]] stage of someone or something, before it has fully [[mature]]d, especially a time of gaining food or experience and growing rather than one of performance.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1883| title=The Edinburgh Review - Volume 158 |author=| page=64| passage=In the fourteenth we find, but still in Latin, a quasi-historical drama, in the '''larva''' stage of monologue recitation, founded on a subject from the national annals—that of Ezzelino, tyrant-duke of Padua.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1909| title=Infinity ; Or, Nature's God |author=Frederick Joseph Duggan | page=58| passage=Man's '''larva''' stage is first announced by strong pathetic squalls; — Conscious knowledge of his helplessness, — dependency, appalls, —  Evokes maternal sympathy,—  for him she will provide,— Most proud mother, happy parent, as he nestles by her side.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|year=1910|month=November|work=The Louisiana School Review |title=Teaching Pupils to Study|author=|volume=18|number=3|page=132|passage=The '''larva''' stage of the child's mind demands much forage material. }}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1915| title=Nervous and Mental Disease Monographs - Volumes 19-22 - |author=| page=34| passage=The '''larva stage''' possesses a libido of nutrition, if I may so express it, but not yet the libido sexualis.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1930 | title=American Childhood - Volume 16 |author=| page=10| passage=After they have fairly emerged from what may be termed the '''larva''' stage, so that they can make their way about, we see them experimenting with their bodies and exploring their surroundings. Babies handle; they taste, they feel with hands and mouths, they look, and they listen; they creep and walk and climb; later they stride, trot, jump, utilizing everything they can find in their play purpose of activity.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1956| title=Debates - Part 1 |author=Gold Coast. Legislative Assembly | page=205| passage=I would call the arrival and settlement of our forefathers in this country which we now call Ghana as the egg stage; the time between the birth of the Fante Confederacy and the time of the first Legislative Council as the '''larva''' stage; the time the Positive Action was declared as the pupa stage; and the 3rd of August, 1956, when the historic motion for independence was moved, as the full-grown stage.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2021| title=The Vision Code: How to Create and Execute a Compelling Vision for Your Business|author=Oleg Konovalov | page=31| passage=A vision in the '''larva''' stage uses our knowledge base to grow. We cannot see this process, but it goes on in the back of our mind, usually without our knowing it.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2021| title=Go to the Next Level|author=Reynaldo J Garcia | page=| passage=We also have been in the '''larva''' stage of life. And many people will never abandon this stage. A '''larva''' is an adult of eighteen years or more. An adult that never grew up and just wakes up, work, pay bills, sleep, breathe, and so on.}}

